---
title: Historical Map
description: Interactive map of historical places in Carrigtwohill parish, including the MTU/CIT village exhibit.
permalink: /map/
layout: layouts/base.njk
maplibre: true
bodyClass: map-page-body
---
<div class="map-page">
  <div class="map-toolbar">
    <div class="map-toolbar-text">
      <h1 class="page-title">Historical Map</h1>
      <p>Satellite view with a slight tilt. Zoom in to see place names. Turn on townlands to show boundaries and names. Red circles are MTU/CIT exhibit films.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="map-toolbar-actions" role="group" aria-label="Map layers">
      <button type="button" id="map-basemap-toggle" class="btn map-ctrl-btn" aria-pressed="true">Street map</button>
      <button type="button" id="map-townlands-toggle" class="btn map-ctrl-btn" aria-pressed="false">Townland borders</button>
      <button type="button" id="map-townland-names-toggle" class="btn map-ctrl-btn" aria-pressed="false">Townland names</button>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="map-frame">
    <div id="chs-map" role="region" aria-label="Carrigtwohill historical map"></div>
    <div id="map-status" class="map-status">Loading map…</div>
  </div>
  <div class="map-legend">
    <span class="legend-places">Parish places</span>
    <span class="legend-mtu">MTU exhibit films</span>
  </div>

  <aside class="map-contribute" aria-labelledby="map-contribute-title">
    <div class="map-contribute-inner">
      <h2 id="map-contribute-title">Help us enrich this map</h2>
      <p>
        Spot a missing place, a story, a photograph, or a correction? Your local knowledge is very welcome —
        this map grows with the community.
      </p>
      <p class="map-contribute-email">
        Email us at
        <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>
        or reach us on social media:
      </p>
      {% set socialClass = "social-nav-map" %}
      {% set socialLabel = "Contact and social links" %}
      {% include "partials/social-icons.njk" %}
      <p class="map-contribute-contact">
        Prefer a form?
        <a href="{{ '/about/contact-us/' | url }}">Use the contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </aside>
</div>
